    "message_1": "For a statistics project, a student measured the number of hours studied per week and the exam scores for 10 students. The data is given below:\n\nHours Studied (x): 6, 8, 4, 7, 9, 5, 7, 3, 6, 8\nExam Scores (y): 75, 82, 63, 80, 90, 70, 82, 60, 72, 81\n\nCalculate the correlation coefficient between hours studied and exam scores.",
    "message_2": "To calculate the correlation coefficient (r) between hours studied (x) and exam scores (y), we will use the following formula:\n\nr = Σ[(xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ)] / √[Σ(xi - x̄)² * Σ(yi - ȳ)²]\n\nFirst, we need to find the mean of x (x̄) and the mean of y (ȳ):\n\nx̄ = (6 + 8 + 4 + 7 + 9 + 5 + 7 + 3 + 6 + 8) / 10 = 63 / 10 = 6.3\nȳ = (75 + 82 + 63 + 80 + 90 + 70 + 82 + 60 + 72 + 81) / 10 = 755 / 10 = 75.5\n\nNext, we will calculate the values of (xi - x̄), (yi - ȳ), (xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ), (xi - x̄)², and (yi - ȳ)² for each data point:\n\n| xi | yi | xi - x̄ | yi - ȳ | (xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ) | (xi - x̄)² | (yi - ȳ)² |\n|----|----|--------|--------|----------------|----------|----------|\n|  6 | 75 |   -0.3 |   -0.5 |          0.15  |     0.09 |     0.25 |\n|  8 | 82 |    1.7 |    6.5 |         11.05  |     2.89 |    42.25 |\n|  4 | 63 |   -2.3 |  -12.5 |         28.75  |     5.29 |   156.25 |\n|  7 | 80 |    0.7 |    4.5 |          3.15  |     0.49 |    20.25 |\n|  9 | 90 |    2.7 |   14.5 |         39.15  |     7.29 |   210.25 |\n|  5 | 70 |   -1.3 |   -5.5 |          7.15  |     1.69 |    30.25 |\n|  7 | 82 |    0.7 |    6.5 |          4.55  |     0.49 |    42.25 |\n|  3 | 60 |   -3.3 |  -15.5 |         51.15  |    10.89 |   240.25 |\n|  6 | 72 |   -0.3 |   -3.5 |          1.05  |     0.09 |    12.25 |\n|  8 | 81 |    1.7 |    5.5 |          9.35  |     2.89 |    30.25 |\n\nNow, we will find the sum of (xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ), the sum of (xi - x̄)², and the sum of (yi - ȳ)²:\n\nΣ(xi - x̄)(yi - ȳ) = 0.15 + 11.05 + 28.75 + 3.15 + 39.15 + 7.15 + 4.55 + 51.15 + 1.05 + 9.35 = 155.5\nΣ(xi - x̄)² = 0.09 + 2.89 + 5.29 + 0.49 + 7.29 + 1.69 + 0.49 + 10.89 + 0.09 + 2.89 = 31.21\nΣ(yi - ȳ)² = 0.25 + 42.25 + 156.25 + 20.25 + 210.25 + 30.25 + 42.25 + 240.25 + 12.25 + 30.25 = 784.5\n\nFinally, we will plug these values into the formula for r:\n\nr = 155.5 / √(31.21 * 784.5) ≈ 155.5 / √(24476.935) ≈ 155.5 / 156.45 ≈ 0.9939\n\nThe correlation coefficient between hours studied and exam scores is approximately 0.9939, indicating a strong positive correlation."
